The paper deals with distance labeling schemes, which are a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and graph theory (cs.DM). The focus is on hub labeling schemes, which are a specific type of distance labeling scheme, and the paper provides lower bounds and constructions for hub labeling in sparse graphs. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to computational geometry (cs.CG) and information theory (cs.IT), as well as communication complexity (cs.CC) due to the use of the Sum-Index problem.
